## Propagating Trace Context Across RabbitMQ

The core issue: RabbitMQ doesn't automatically carry W3C `traceparent`/`tracestate` headers. You must **inject** context when publishing and **extract** it when consuming.

### Publisher (Service A)

```csharp
using System.Diagnostics;

// Define a shared ActivitySource for your messaging
static readonly ActivitySource MessagingSource = new("MyApp.Messaging");

// When publishing:
using var activity = MessagingSource.StartActivity("order.publish", ActivityKind.Producer);

var props = channel.CreateBasicProperties();
props.Headers ??= new Dictionary<string, object>();

// Inject current trace context into message headers
if (Activity.Current != null)
{
    props.Headers["traceparent"] = Activity.Current.Id;           // W3C trace id
    props.Headers["tracestate"]  = Activity.Current.TraceStateString ?? "";
}

channel.BasicPublish(exchange, routingKey, props, body);
```

### Consumer (Service B)

```csharp
var consumer = new EventingBasicConsumer(channel);
consumer.Received += (_, ea) =>
{
    // Extract propagated context from headers
    ActivityContext parentContext = default;

    if (ea.BasicProperties.Headers?.TryGetValue("traceparent", out var raw) == true)
    {
        var traceparent = Encoding.UTF8.GetString((byte[])raw);
        ActivityContext.TryParse(traceparent, null, out parentContext);
    }

    // Start a new activity linked to the producer's trace
    using var activity = MessagingSource.StartActivity(
        "order.consume",
        ActivityKind.Consumer,
        parentContext);   // ← this is the key — sets the parent

    // Process the message…
};
```

### Wire it up in `Program.cs`

```csharp
builder.Services.AddOpenTelemetry()
    .WithTracing(t => t
        .AddSource("MyApp.Messaging")       // your custom ActivitySource
        .AddAspNetCoreInstrumentation()
        .AddOtlpExporter());                // or Jaeger/Zipkin
```

### Why this works

| Step | What happens |
|---|---|
| **Inject** | `Activity.Current.Id` serialises the W3C `traceparent` (trace-id + span-id) into a RabbitMQ header |
| **Extract** | Consumer parses the header back into an `ActivityContext` |
| **Link** | Passing `parentContext` to `StartActivity` makes the consumer span a **child** of the producer span — same trace ID |

### Tips

- **MassTransit / NServiceBus** do this automatically — if you use either, just enable the OpenTelemetry source (`MassTransit` / `NServiceBus.Core`) and it works out of the box.
- For the raw `RabbitMQ.Client`, the injection/extraction above is the standard pattern.
- Make sure both services export to the **same backend** (OTLP collector, Jaeger, etc.) so the trace is stitched together.
